>   Eric> 	Window borders disappear now when I maximize a window.
>   Eric> The window is truly maximized.
> Does this affect the ability to normalize the window?
Nope.  As long as you have a Maximize/restore button on the title bar.  I
guess I was not totally clear, the title bar is still mapped.

This is the first step in a greater plan.  The one thing that I love about
the Mac is the global title bar.  I am also writing a module that behaves
like that title bar.  It will have a label area to hold the name of the
window with the current focus, user defineable buttons and menus, somewhat
like GoodStuff, etc.  When a window gets maximized in this scheme, it
loses its title bar, and covers the entire screen except the global title
bar.

>   Eric> 	Also, the title bar now extends for the entire width
>   Eric> of the parent frame, the side borders stop at the bottom of
>   Eric> the title bar.  Also, there is no top border (that is what the
>   Eric> title bar is for).
> What about Style NoTitle? I have a lot of windows that have the sizing bars,
> but no title bar.
That is in the works.  When there is no title bar, there will be a top
border.

As for screen shots, I am fairly well firewalled here.  I have no external
web page that I could post them on, and I am loath to post a binary to a
list.  Lemme know, and I will mail something personally.

ericb

